[VISUAL: A grand staff showing the finale chord: C major, six voices (basses on C1, cellos on C2, violas on G3, woodwinds on E4, brass on G4, violins on C5), all whole notes, eight-beat duration. To the right of the staff, a dynamic marking shows \"pp → ff\" with a crescendo hairpin spanning eight beats. Six note-sprites (16×16 whole notes) are positioned near each note; as the crescendo progresses (visually indicated by a timeline bar below the staff), the sprites grow slightly larger and bob more energetically, matching the dynamic build. The whole image conveys a sense of *swelling* sound — quiet to loud, thin to full.]

```scheme
;; Finale artifact: a sustained, crescendoing C major orchestral chord (tutti, 8 beats).

(transport/tempo 60)

